 The accident took place on the corner of Walter Sisulu- and SADC Street at roughly 11:00 this morning. The traffic department has released no information on the cause of the accident, but it is known that the motorist driving the silver Nissan was taken into custody at the scene. The motorist driving the silver Nissan was taken into custody and is seated in the traffic control vehicle.  The vehicle that was rear-ended was not carrying any medical waste at the time, and no serious injuries or damages were sustained. The scene was controlled by the traffic police and fire brigade and has since been cleared up. The silver Nissan was moved to a parking area to make way for traffic.  Hawks members sent to jail for fraud WATCH: The Place of Refuge – Once a vibrant village, now a ghost town WATCH: Robbery caught on video, police looking for suspects Three counts of poaching in one week – and the toll keeps rising   • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za